Pretoria - Touring the Segaetsho Cultural Village in the Sun City Resort is an experience out of this world. Pretoria News was part of a media team invited to experience and explore their new and revamped outdoor adventures. Through songs and dance, a group of vibrant and enthusiastic young performers give you an insight into South African traditions and the history of the people of North West province. Their performance make one instantly fall in love with tradition, the mind blowing moves and voices keeping the audience glued to them throughout. For close to an hour, they performed Setswana and IsiZulu dances accompanied by poems and of cause the audience was engaged; as they pulled one or two people to the platform to dance with them. To view this video please enable JavaScript, and consider upgrading to a web browser that
